Which of the following time signatures have standard notation? <image 1>

A. BC
B. AD
C. AC
D. AB

To determine which time signatures have standard notation, we need to identify the standard time signatures among the given options.

- A. \( \frac{6}{8} \)
- B. \( \frac{3}{4} \)
- C. \( \frac{2}{4} \)
- D. \( \frac{12}{8} \)

Standard time signatures typically include:
- \( \frac{4}{4} \) (common time)
- \( \frac{3}{4} \) (waltz time)
- \( \frac{2}{4} \) (two beats per measure)
- \( \frac{6}{8} \) (six eighth notes per measure)

Given this information, the standard time signatures in the image are:
- A. \( \frac{6}{8} \)
- B. \( \frac{3}{4} \)
- C. \( \frac{2}{4} \)

Therefore, the correct answer is:

C. AC
